     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>To my worthy friend Tho. Adams on his
HERBALL.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>THe Herbes which these dead leaues now bring,</l>
      <l>Thy liuing voice did sweetly sing.</l>
      <l>That thy transported Hearers thought</l>
      <l>A PARADISE before them brought.</l>
      <l>As if their inward eyes had seene</l>
      <l>Another EDEN fresh and greene.</l>
      <l>How they will smell, or taste, thus sent,</l>
      <l>Will be perceiu'd in the euent.</l>
      <l>I stay no censures; for my part,</l>
      <l>May they grow greene still in my hart.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>VV. B.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
